                    <div class='commenttext'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span style="font-size: 120%;">#31 Dave</span></strong> @ 6:11 pm May 9th, 2008</span><br />
<p>Folks,</p>
<p>It&#8217;s healthier and more economical to not use the &#8220;Instant&#8221; oatmeal. I make my own &#8216;packets&#8217; of oatmeal with regular quaker oats. 1/2 cup oatmeal, 1 cup water, zap it 1 minute, stir, zap it 90 more seconds. While microwaving, I use my apple corer/slicer and then a knife to make 12 apple chunks (eat 3 slices, cut the other 3 into 4 pieces). Stir it into the oatmeal, top with cinnamon. Pounds slide off.</p>
<p>Dave</p>
</div>

