                    <div class='commenttext'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span style="font-size: 120%;">#81 Lisa</span></strong> @ 11:15 am May 12th, 2008</span><br />
<p>Lise: good question about the boiling over. First, I cook my steel cut oats in a glass batter bowl (the kind with a handle on the side; like an 8 cup liquid measuring cup)so it is tall, set the microwave to 6 minutes (your microwave may very), and then SET THE POWER TO 50%. Lowering the power is the key. Microwaves don&#8217;t really lower the power. They just are sometimes on and sometimes off. This is actually rather cool to watch as it bubbles up when the microwave is nuking it, then all the oatmeal settles down while it is not nuking, then the volcano builds up again, etc. No lid.</p>
</div>

