                    <div class='commenttext'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span style="font-size: 120%;">#91 djc</span></strong> @ 4:24 pm May 13th, 2008</span><br />
<p>regarding steel cut oats in the slow cooker &#8211; I put 1/4 cup of the steel cut oats in a standard cereal bowl with 1 cup of almond or soy milk with a dash of salt. I set a trivet in the slow cooker insert and add a couple of inches of water to the bottom. Then I cover the cereal bowl with foil and set it on the trivet, then put the lid on. Set it on the low setting to cook overnight &#8211; comes out wonderfully creamy, and only one bowl to soak clean.</p>
